Fast-rising Nigerian singer, Adewale. O. Adebayo better known by his stage name, B Naira is blessing his fans with new music titled, “Fall on Me”. The new song is coming on the heels of the entrepreneur cum singer acquiring a new whip estimated at N91,935,000 ($300,000). The artist who is known for his flamboyant and luxurious lifestyle on his Instagram page (@bnaira01) took to the platform to share photos of his new whip and his uncontainable excitement over the new acquisition. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-939385 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bnaira.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1600" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bnaira.jpg 1080w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bnaira-478x598.jpg 478w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bnaira-922x1152.jpg 922w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bnaira-446x557.jpg 446w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bnaira-891x1114.jpg 891w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bnaira-192x240.jpg 192w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bnaira-384x480.jpg 384w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bnaira-480x600.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> He wrote in one of the photos, “I feel very honoured to be joining the Ferrari family and becoming a part of the most prestigious team in the history of Formula One. #mynewrarri #ferrari #sellfastpayfast @sellfastpayfast” In another photo, he reveals that he only acquired the whip just so he could be taking photos with it. “I bought this Ride Just to Take photos – Abeg make una No Vex cus it’s photo season  #na dem go tayaaa for this tire,” he wrote. To celebrate his new whip, he decided to release “Fall on me”, which has  since been dubbed as a daily inspiration for hustlers out there. “Fall on me” is available on all Digital streaming platforms and can be downloaded here.